    {
      "lineNumber": 1,
      "text": "Office Memorandum • UNITED STATES GOVERNMENT",
      "status": "permanent_unresolved",
      "unresolvedReason": "other_documented"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 2,
      "status": "blank"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 3,
      "text": "TO      : DIRECTOR, FBI",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 4,
      "text": "DATE: January 31, 1949",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 5,
      "status": "blank"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 6,
      "text": "FROM    : S.A.C., SAN ANTONIO",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 7,
      "status": "blank"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 8,
      "text": "SUBJECT: PROTECTION OF VITAL INSTALLATIONS",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 9,
      "text": "BUREAU FILE # 65-58300",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 10,
      "status": "blank"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 11,
      "text": "INITIAL declassified",
      "status": "permanent_unresolved",
      "unresolvedReason": "other_documented"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 12,
      "text": "[unclear] 8/31/77",
      "status": "permanent_unresolved",
      "unresolvedReason": "other_documented"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 13,
      "text": "[unclear]",
      "status": "permanent_unresolved",
      "unresolvedReason": "other_documented"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 14,
      "status": "blank"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 15,
      "text": "At recent Weekly Intelligence Conferences of G-2, ONI, OSI, and F.B.I.,",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 16,
      "text": "in the Fourth Army Area, Officers of G-2, Fourth Army have discussed the",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 17,
      "text": "matter of \"Unidentified Aircraft\" or \"Unidentified Aerial Phenomena\" otherwise",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 18,
      "text": "known as \"Flying Discs\", \"Flying Saucers\", and \"Balls of Fire\". This matter",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 19,
      "text": "is considered top secret by Intelligence Officers of both the Army and the",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 20,
      "text": "Air Forces.",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 21,
      "status": "blank"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 22,
      "text": "It is well known that there have been during the past two years reports from",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 23,
      "text": "the various parts of the country of the sighting of unidentified aerial",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 24,
      "text": "objects which have been called in newspaper parlance \"flying discs\" and",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 25,
      "text": "\"flying saucers\". The first such sightings were reported from Sweden, and",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 26,
      "text": "it was thought that the objects, the nature of which was unknown, might have",
      "status": "permanent_unresolved",
      "unresolvedReason": "other_documented"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 27,
      "text": "originated in Russia.",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 28,
      "status": "blank"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 29,
      "text": "In July 1948 an unidentified aircraft was \"seen\" by an Eastern Airlines",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 30,
      "text": "Pilot and Co-Pilot and one or more passengers of the Eastern Airlines Plane",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 31,
      "text": "over Montgomery, Alabama. This aircraft was reported to be of an uncon-",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 32,
      "text": "ventional type without wings and resembled generally a \"rocket ship\" of the",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 33,
      "text": "type depicted in comic strips. It was reported to have had windows; to",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 34,
      "text": "have been larger than the Eastern Airlines plane, and to have been traveling",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 35,
      "text": "at an estimated speed of 2700 miles an hour. It appeared out of a thunder-",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 36,
      "text": "head ahead of the Eastern Airlines plane and immediately disappeared in another",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 37,
      "text": "cloud narrowly missing a collision with the Eastern Airlines plane. No",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 38,
      "text": "sound or air disturbance was noted in connection with this appearance.",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 39,
      "status": "blank"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 40,
      "text": "During the past two months various sightings of unexplained phenomena have",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 41,
      "text": "been reported in the vicinity of the A.E.C. Installation at Los Alamos,",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 42,
      "text": "New Mexico, where these phenomena now appear to be concentrated. During",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 43,
      "text": "December 1948 on the 5th, 6th, 7th, 8th, 11th, 13, 14th, 20th and 28th",
      "status": "permanent_unresolved",
      "unresolvedReason": "other_documented"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 44,
      "text": "sightings of unexplained phenomena were made near Los Alamos by Special",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 45,
      "text": "Agents of the Office of Special Investigation; Airline Pilots; Military",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 46,
      "text": "Pilots, Los Alamos Security Inspectors, and private citizens. On",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 47,
      "text": "January 6, 1949, another similar object was sighted in the same area.",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 48,
      "status": "blank"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 49,
      "text": "67c",
      "status": "permanent_unresolved",
      "unresolvedReason": "other_documented"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 50,
      "text": "A meteorologist of some note, has been generally in",
      "status": "permanent_unresolved",
      "unresolvedReason": "other_documented"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 51,
      "text": "charge of the observations near Los Alamos, attempting to learn character-",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 52,
      "text": "istics of the unexplained phenomena.",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 53,
      "status": "blank"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 54,
      "text": "Up to this time little concrete information has been obtained.",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 55,
      "status": "blank"
    },
